title: Practice Question: Will there be a new prime minister of the United Kingdom before 1 August 2018?
description: The Prime Minister of the United Kingdom is the highest elected office in the United Kingdom. The current Prime Minister is Theresa May, who took over from David Cameron on 13 July 2016.

title: Practice Question: What will be the daily closing price of gold on 12 March 2018 in USD?
description: This question will be resolved using the last daily London Bullion Market Association (LBMA) Gold Price USD (PM) (http://www.lbma.org.uk/pricing-and-statistics) for the date of interest. The relevant data is available by selecting 'Table' and referring to the 'PM' column under 'USD.' Question will be suspended on the day before the date of interest and resolved the day after the date of interest.

title: Will Ireland's referendum to repeal the Eighth Amendment pass?
description: The referendum on Ireland's current abortion ban is scheduled for 25 May 2018 (Image, Department of Taoiseach).

title: Will the Council of the European Union make an Article 7.1 determination against a member state before 8 September 2018?
description: Article 7.1 enables the Council of the European Union, acting by a majority of four fifths of its members after obtaining the consent of the European Parliament, to determine whether a member state's actions risk a serious breach of the values referred to in Article 2 of the Treaty of the European Union (EUR-Lex, Politico). In December 2017 the European Commission asked the European Council to consider an Article 7.1 determination against Poland, and some Members of the European Parliament are looking into Hungary (European Commission, Deutsche Welle, European Parliament).

title: How many deaths perpetrated by Boko Haram will the Council on Foreign Relations report for June 2018?
description: The Council on Foreign Relations (CFR) Nigeria Security Tracker reports on countrywide violence stemming from political, economic and social grievances. The question will be resolved using data downloaded from CFR at: Google Docs Spreadsheet. Refer to the sheet entitled ‘NST Main Dataset.’ The count of deaths for the period of interest is obtained by summing the ‘Total Deaths’ column for events in which Boko Haram is identified as a perpetrator (in the ‘Boko Haram (P)’ column) and ‘Date’ falls in the period of interest. Question will be resolved when the data are released, likely the week after the period of interest.

title: Will the Afghan Taliban participate in official peace talks with the governments of Afghanistan or the United States before 8 September 2018?
description: In February Afghan President Ashraf Ghani announced an initiative to bring the Taliban to the negotiating table, meanwhile the Taliban has been pushing for direct talks with Washington (RFERL, Atlantic Council, NY Times). Official talks with splinter/breakaway groups of the Taliban will not count (e.g.,BBC, NY Times).

title: Will American pastor Andrew Brunson leave Turkey before 8 September 2018?
description: Brunson was imprisoned in Turkey for 18 months on terrorism charges but was recently transferred to house arrest (https://www.voanews.com/a/us-pastor-richard-brunson-trial-turkey/4350577.html). A “yes” resolution will require a credible report confirming that Brunson departed Turkey before 8 September 2018.

title: Will Iran execute or be targeted in an acknowledged national military attack before 1 July 2018?
description: "Acknowledged” means the government of the country executing the attack claims responsibility for it. A “national military attack” includes the employment of conventional and unconventional weapons by one country’s national military forces on another country’s military, military assets, or territory, including citizens located within that territory, but excluding territorial waters, foreign missions, and/or exclusive economic zones. A “cyber” attack will not qualify as a “national military attack.” Attacks by specific military or paramilitary units or non-state actors will not qualify as “national military attacks” unless the government claims responsibility for them.
clarification: This question was resolved on 18 April as "yes." After further review, we have re-opened the question. While news reports do indicate an attack on Iranian military, Israel has not claimed responsibility.  According to the resolution criteria the attack must be acknowledged, meaning "the government of the country executing the attack claims responsibility for it.”

title: How many terrorist incidents with 15 or more dead (victims + perpetrators) will occur in August 2018 as reported by Wikipedia?
description: This question will be resolved using the number of terrorist incidents reported in Wikipedia (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_terrorist_incidents) in which 15 or more deaths, both victims and perpetrators, are reported for the month of interest. If deaths are reported as a range for an incident, the lower bound will be used to determine if the event qualifies as 15 or more. Question will be resolved based on the data reported in Wikipedia at 11:59 PM ET on the first day of the following month (e.g., data reported 1 February at 11:59 PM ET if question concerns terrorist incidents in January).

title: Before 8 September 2018, will Chinese tariffs on U.S. soybeans take effect?

title: Will the Government of Canada issue a travel advisory of "Avoid all travel" for Nicaragua between 29 June 2018 and 31 August 2018?

The question will resolve as "yes" if, during the period of interest, an advisory of interest is listed in the ‘Risk Level(s)’ tab with 'Last updated' in the period of interest. Regional advisories will count toward resolution; that is, if an advisory of interest is issued for even one region of the country of interest, the question will resolve as "yes."

title: Will S&P, Moody's, or Fitch issue a sovereign credit rating for Iran before 8 September 2018?
description: Any issuer rating will count (e.g., short-term, long-term, foreign currency, local currency, preliminary, or final). A credit rating from S&P, Moody's, or Fitch would facilitate Iran's integration into the global financial system (PressTV, Gulf News). Capital Intelligence has affirmed Iran's long- and short-term local and foreign currency ratings (Capital Intelligence Ratings), but none of the three agencies in question have issued a rating in recent years (Financial Tribune, Moodys).

This question will be resolved based on initial values typically released the first week of the following month.

title: How many positive influenza virus detections will FluNet record for China between 12 March 2018 and 18 March 2018 (epidemiological week 11)?
description: FluNet ( http://www.who.int/influenza/gisrs_laboratory/flunet/en/) is the World Health Organization's global web-based tool for influenza virological surveillance. Relevant data can be accessed via FluNet functions, 'Download influenza laboratory surveillance data from any week' at: http://apps.who.int/flumart/Default?ReportNo=12. Select by: 'Country, area or territory'; Filter by: 'Country of interest', Year from: '2018', Week: '1', Year to: '2018' Week: '53', and then click 'Display report.' This question will be resolved by using the sum of values reported in the ‘Total number of influenza positive viruses’ (or .csv ‘ALL_INF’) column for the country of interest for all reporting weeks within the period of interest. Question will be suspended on the last day of the period of interest and resolved when data for the period of interest is released.
clarification: Due to recent volatile data revisions, this question will be resolved four weeks after close based on data available at the end of epidemiological week 15 (15 April 2018).

title: Will Ethiopia be under a state of emergency on 20 August 2018?
description: Ethiopia has been under one state of emergency or another for much of the last few years, with the most recent state of emergency declared on 13 February 2018 following the resignation of Prime Minister Hailemariam Desalegn (Eyewitness News, Reuters). The state of emergency is slated to last six months from when it was declared (Ethiopian Government, Aljazeera, Aljazeera).
option_2: Yes, but only in some areas

title: Before 8 September 2018, will India sign either of the two remaining defense foundational agreements with the U.S.?
description: The U.S. proposed three defense foundational agreements -- the Logistics Supply Agreement (LSA), the Basic Exchange and Cooperation Agreement (BECA), and the Communications Compatibility and Security Arrangement (COMCASA), earlier called the Communication Interoperability and Security Memorandum Agreement (CISMOA) (The Diplomat, The Diplomat). India signed the LSA in August 2016, but it has not yet agreed to the other two (Defense News, India Times). Renaming of the BECA or COMCASA agreements will not affect the resolution of this question.

title: Before 8 September 2018, will Poland, Estonia, Latvia, or Lithuania accuse Russia of intervening militarily in its territory without permission?
description: If the relevant governments are overthrown, third-party accusations will count. Examples of past accusations of Russian military intervention include Georgia's claim that Russia invaded its territory in August 2008 (Belfast Telegraph), Ukraine's claim that Russia invaded Crimea in February 2014 (Suptnik News), Ukraine's condemnation of illegal Russian fighters in Eastern Ukraine in June 2014 (Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Ukraine), and Ukraine's statement in August 2014 that Russian military forces had crossed the border and were actively engaged in fighting (The Guardian).
clarification: Accusations of Russian cyber attacks alone will not suffice to resolve the question.

The cabinet approval rate is reported as 支持する (Support to) in the first table 内閣：安倍内閣 (Cabinet: Abe Cabinet) on that page. Months are indicated by their corresponding number (e.g. 1月 = January). If NHK conducts more than one survey in a month, question resolution will be based on the first set of results posted. The question will be resolved using Google Translate services.
clarification: In the event of Abe resigning as Prime Minister, this question will be resolved based on whatever Cabinet was in place at the time the survey was conducted.

title: How many cases of MERS-CoV in humans will EMPRES-i record in Saudi Arabia in July 2018?
description: EMPRES Global Animal Disease Information System (EMPRES-i) is the Food and Agricultural Organization (FAO) of the United Nation's global web-based tool for animal disease surveillance. To access the data from http://empres-i.fao.org: - Click on the map; - Click Advanced Search in the top right corner- Set OBSERVATION DATES to cover the time period of interest;- Check MERS-CoV from DISEASE LIST- Check Saudi Arabia under Asia from ADMINISTRATIVE UNITS; - Check human from ANIMALS AFFECTED; - Click Find; - Export to CSV. Outcome will be determined by the sum of the values reported in the "humansAffected" column. This question will be closed on 31 July 2018 and resolved using data accessed on 20 August 2018 between 10:00 AM and 4:00 PM ET.

title: Will there be a locally-transmitted case of the Zika virus in Ukraine, Russia, Georgia or Armenia between 1 June 2018 and 31 August 2018?

Imported cases (e.g., where the patient traveled to an endemic country, contracted the disease, and brought it home) do not meet the resolution criteria, though a locally-transmitted case which originates from an imported case does. If there is no indication of whether a case was locally-transmitted, this question will resolve as “no.”

title: Will there be a locally-transmitted case of the Zika virus in Singapore between 1 April 2018 and 31 May 2018?
description: The disease must have been contracted in the country of interest for this question to resolve as "yes." If there is no indication of whether a case was locally-transmitted, this question will resolve as “no.”

title: When will the Russian Ministry of Justice next designate a media outlet as a foreign agent?

The following month, nine entities were designated as foreign agents, including Voice of America and Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty (The Ministry of Justice of the Russian Federation, Reuters, NY Times). The designation of individual journalists and bloggers as foreign agents will not count (e.g., RFERL).

title: Will Somalia's President Mohamed Abdullahi Mohamed experience a significant leadership disruption before 1 September 2018?
description: A “significant leadership disruption” includes confirmed reports that the leader: has resigned, has formally left office, has been forcibly removed from office for 10 or more consecutive days, has fled or been exiled from office for 10 or more consecutive days, has died, has been medically incapacitated or hospitalized for 10 or more consecutive days, or his/her whereabouts have been unknown for 10 or more consecutive days.

title: Before 1 June 2018, will any of the signatories to the Iran nuclear deal announce they are withdrawing?
description: China, France, Germany, Russia, the United Kingdom, the United States, the European Union, and Iran signed a Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA) in July 2015 (). Iran has threatened to withdraw and the United States decertified the deal but kept sanctions waivers in place (Reuters, Washington Post).
clarification: A twitter announcement, on its own, will not be sufficient to close the question.

title: Before 1 September 2018, how many countries, from among Saudi Arabia, the UAE, Bahrain, and Egypt, will return their ambassador to Qatar?
description: Saudi Arabia, the UAE, Bahrain, and Egypt severed diplomatic relations with Qatar in June 2017 (Harvard Political Review, The National, Center for Strategic and International Studies).

title: What will be the South Korean Won to one U.S. Dollar daily exchange rate on 29 June 2018?
description: This question will be resolved using the daily rate reported by Federal Reserve Economic Data (FRED) for the date of interest (https://fred.stlouisfed.org/series/DEXKOUS). Question will be closed the day before the date of interest and resolved when the data is released, usually on Monday of the following week.

title: How many battle deaths will ACLED record in Afghanistan in April 2018?
description: The Armed Conflict Location and Event Dataset (ACLED) summarizes press reports on conflict and protest events in Africa and parts of Asia. The relevant data can be accessed using the export tool at https://www.acleddata.com/data/: set ‘From’ to the first day of the period of interest; ‘To’ to the last day of the period of interest; and ‘Country’ to the country of interest. Click ‘Export.’ The count of battle deaths for the period of interest is obtained by summing the 'fatalities’ column for events in which ‘event_type’ is Battle-Government regains territory, Battle-No change of territory, or Battle-Non-state actor overtakes territory. Question will be resolved when the relevant data are first released.

title: Will Israel execute or be targeted in an acknowledged national military attack before 1 July 2018?
description: "Acknowledged” means the government of the country executing the attack claims responsibility for it. A “national military attack” includes the employment of conventional or unconventional weapons by one country’s national military forces on another country’s military, military assets, or territory, including citizens located within that territory, but excluding territorial waters, foreign missions, and/or exclusive economic zones. A “cyber” attack will not qualify as a “national military attack.” Attacks by specific military or paramilitary units or non-state actors will not qualify as “national military attacks” unless the government claims responsibility for them.

title: Will Armenia's Prime Minister Nikol Pashinyan experience a significant leadership disruption before 1 September 2018?
description: A “significant leadership disruption” includes confirmed reports that the leader: has resigned, has formally left office, has been forcibly removed from office for 10 or more consecutive days, has fled or been exiled from office for 10 or more consecutive days, has died, has been medically incapacitated or hospitalized for 10 or more consecutive days, or his/her whereabouts have been unknown for 10 or more consecutive days.

title: What will be the long-term interest rate for Portugal (PRT) in April 2018?
description: This question will be resolved using monthly data reported by the Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development (OECD) at https://data.oecd.org/interest/long-term-interest-rates.htm). Data is retrievable via download or on the 'Long-term interest rates' table on the web site. The relevant country can be found in the HIGHLIGHTED COUNTRIES or LOCATION field, and the relevant time period can be found in the TIME field. Question will be resolved when the data is released, likely the month after the period of interest.
clarification: This question will be resolved based on data precise to the hundredths place. When selecting the country of interest, do not remove the countries that are highlighted by default. Doing this will display data to the correct precision.

title: Will ACLED record any civilian fatalities in Ghana in June 2018?
Will a Loya Jirga convene in Afghanistan before 8 September 2018?
description: The September 2014 agreement that produced Afghanistan's current national unity government called for the convocation of a Loya Jirga (Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty, , Afghan Embassy). However, the Loya Jirga has not yet convened and the stability of Afghanistan's government remains tenuous (Afghanistan Times, 1 TV News, Reuters, Tolo News).

title: Will FEWS NET publish a Food Security Alert with "famine" and "Ethiopia" in its headline between 27 April 2018 and 31 July 2018?
description: The Famine Early Warning Systems Network provides early warning and analysis on acute food insecurity around the world. Question will resolve as "yes" if FEWS NET publishes one or more Food Security Alert(s) in the time period of interest that includes the words "famine" and the country of interest in its headline (FEWS NET Search).

title: When will the cash buyer bid price per tonne of cobalt on the London Metal Exchange first reach US $100,000?
description: Cobalt, essential for the lithium-ion batteries used in smartphones and electric vehicles, is in high demand and prices have been soaring (Bloomberg, Stratfor, Financial Times). This question will be resolved based on the London Metal Exchange official price per tonne of cobalt for the "Cash Buyer" Contract Type at (www.lme.com. For historical prices, see here.

How many positive influenza virus detections will FluNet record for Australia between 30 July 2018 and 19 August 2018 (epidemiological weeks 31-33, inclusive)?
description: FluNet is the World Health Organization's global web-based tool for influenza virological surveillance. This question will be resolved by using the sum of values reported in the ‘Total number of influenza positive viruses’ (or .csv ‘ALL_INF’) column for the country of interest for all reporting weeks within the period of interest. This question will be resolved by consulting the source between 10:00 AM and 4:00 PM ET starting on 24 September 2018 and each Monday thereafter until data are posted. Resolution will be based on the value observed at the time of source consultation.

title: Will the WHO declare a Public Health Emergency of International Concern (PHEIC) before 1 September 2018?
description: Question will resolve as “yes” if the World Health Organization (WHO) declares a PHEIC via WHO Statements from the International Health Regulations (IHR) Emergency Committee during the period of interest. Past examples of PHEIC declarations include an Ebola Statement and a Zika Statement.

title: Before 8 September 2018, will the Council of the European Union adopt a directive on taxation of digital business activities?
description: "On 21 March 2018, the European Commission proposed new rules on the taxation of digital business activities of large tech companies like Google, Facebook, and Amazon (The Guardian, European Commission). For more information on EU directives and the Council of the European Union's role in the legislative process see: Europa, EuroParl . The adoption of a directive on taxation of digital business activities via the enhanced cooperation procedure would count (Europa). "

title: Before 1 August 2018, will the Moroccan government and the Polisario Front meet for official negotiations over Western Sahara?
description: Negotiations between the Moroccan government and the Polisario Front over disputed territory have been stalled since 2012. Separate meetings recently initiated by a UN Secretary General envoy to the region could spur a new round of negotiations (United Nations, Morocco World News, The Citizen).

title: Before 8 September 2018, will a new Italian government receive a vote of confidence from both houses of Parliament?
description: On 4 March 2018, Italy held general elections (The Local). The results did not reveal a clear leader among the parties, leading to protracted coalition negotiations (Politico, Reuters). Per Article 94 of the Italian constitution, any new government must receive a vote of confidence from both houses of Parliament (Senato de Repubblica).

title: How many material conflict events involving Occupied Palestinian Territory will ICEWS record in March 2018?
description: This question will be resolved using event data collected by the Worldwide Integrated Conflict Early Warning System (W-ICEWS or simply ICEWS - https://www.lockheedmartin.com/us/products/W-ICEWS.html), which can be accessed here: https://github.com/gfchallenge/gfc/tree/master/data/ICEWS.  The files entitled Events_YYYY-MM_Factiva.csv contain events that occurred in month MM of year YYYY, whereas the files entitled ReleaseXXX_Factiva.csv each contain a few weeks’ worth of events, spanning the end of 2015 (Release 272) to the present. ICEWS event data are extracted from the Factiva news database, which draws from a multilingual roster of over 6,000 news sources from around the world. These event data are then assigned event type codes based on the Conflict Events and Mediation Observations (CAMEO) event coding ontology (see http://eventdata.parusanalytics.com/cameo.dir/CAMEO.Manual.1.1b3.pdf).This question will be resolved by counting the number of event records for which: 'Event.Date' falls in the period of interest; 'CAMEO code' is three digits equal to: 14x, 15x, 17x, 18x, 19x, 20x, or four digits equal to: 14xx, 15xx, 17xx, 18xx, 19xx, 20xx (where x=any number); and 'Country' is the country of interest.

title: Will a FARC candidate win a seat in the Colombian Senate or House of Representatives in the upcoming legislative elections?
description: Legislative elections are scheduled for March 11, 2018. The Colombian peace agreement with the guerrilla rebel movement ensures that former members will be able to vote and run as candidates for the legislature and president. It also guarantees that Fuerza Alternativa Revolucionaria del Común (FARC) will hold a minimum of five seats in both the Senate and House. If FARC does not win enough seats in the election then they will be granted the requisite number of seats in the 2018–2022 session (https://www.cnn.com/2017/04/28/americas/colombia-farc-senate/index.html). Question will resolve as “yes” only if a FARC candidate wins in the election.

title: Will Cuba's National assembly elect Miguel Diaz-Canel Bermudez as President of Cuba’s Council of States and the Council of Ministers on 19 April 2018?
description: Cuba's National Assembly is expected to elect a president on April 19, 2018 ( https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cuba-election/cuba-holds-one-party-vote-as-post-castro-era-looms-idUSKCN1GN05H,Miami Herald 2 ).

title: How many missile test events will North Korea conduct in May 2018?
description: This question will be resolved based on the missile test events reported in the Timeline Table of Wikipedia's North Korean Missile Test Page at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_North_Korean_missile_tests. Each row in the Timeline table counts as one event. The final Wikipedia edit made on the first day of the following month (e.g.,1 February for a question about January) will be used for resolution.

Before 8 September 2018, will Saudi Arabia announce that it is ending the blockade of Yemen's Hudaydah port?
description: Temporary lifting of the blockade or partial lifting of the blockade for specific purposes (e.g., humanitarian aid) is not sufficient to close the question. In November 2017, Saudi Arabia and its allies imposed a blockade on Yemen (US News, NY Times). This included the Houthi-controlled Hudaydah port, which accounted for a majority of commercial imports to the country (ReliefWeb). Saudi Arabia announced it would temporarily ease the blockade but not end it (The Guardian, ReliefWeb, Vice News).

title: What will be the maximum sea ice extent on the Baffin Bay Gulf of St. Lawrence between 21 March 2018 and 10 April 2018?
description: This question will be resolved using the Multisensor Analyzed Sea Ice Extent - Northern Hemisphere (MASIE-NH) data reported by NOAA's National Snow & Ice Data Center (http://nsidc.org/data/masie). To access the relevant data: - Click the ‘Download Data’ button, - Select 'Daily Sea Ice Extent Values: Comma Separated Values (CSV) file' - Look at the column for the relevant region. If the maximum occurs before the close date, the question will be closed retroactively with the first date of the maximum as the end date of the question.

title: How many 'hacking or malware (HACK)' data breaches will Privacy Rights Clearinghouse record in April 2018?
description: This question will be resolved using Privacy Rights Clearinghouse's Chronology of Data Breaches (https://www.privacyrights.org/data-breaches). To access the relevant data: *UPDATED instructions as of 27 March (see 'clarification' tab)* - Select 'Hacking or Malware (HACK)' as the type of breach, - Click 'Search Data Breaches', - Download the 'Data Breach File', - Count the number of entries, for all organizations, in which 'Date Made Public' falls in the month of interest. The question will be resolved using data from the last day of the following month.
clarification:
Because some events listed in the Privacy Rights Clearinghouse may have occurred in 2017 or earlier but not made public until 2018, you should download all available data and sort by ‘Date Made Public’ to count the number of entries made public in a given month. Updated resolution criteria will state: 

This question will be resolved using Privacy Rights Clearinghouse's Chronology of Data Breaches (https://www.privacyrights.org/data-breaches). To access the relevant data: 
- Select 'Hacking or Malware (HACK)' as the type of breach, 
- Click 'Search Data Breaches', 
- Download the 'Data Breach File', 
- Count the number of entries, for all organizations, in which 'Date Made Public' falls in the month of interest (if necessary, sort on ‘Date Made Public’). 
The question will be resolved using data from the last day of the following month.

title: What will be the monthly Period-over-Period change in the consumer price index (CPI) for Guinea-Bissau in March 2018 (Month 3)?
description: This question will be resolved using data from the International Monetary Fund (http://data.imf.org/regular.aspx?key=61015893), and can be found after ensuring the country of interest is selected from the Country drop down menu, and 'Consumer Price Index, All Items' is selected from the Indicator drop down menu. The relevant row is: '[Country of Interest], Consumer Price Index, All Items,' and the relevant column will be '2018 [Month of Interest].' Question will be resolved based on initially reported values expected to be published the first week of the following month.
clarification: The IMF CPI tables for Guinea-Bissau for 2017M06 and 2017M07 show two outlying data points compared to other months. We suspect that the original data for 2017M06 from which these outliers were calculated was processed (or submitted) incorrectly at IMF. However, these outliers do not significantly change our answer bins. Because IMF is an authoritative source of global financial statistics, we have no reason to suspect at this time that other data on the portal is incorrect.

title: How many earthquakes of magnitude 5 or stronger will occur worldwide in March 2018?
description: This question will be resolved using the United States Geological Survey's Earthquake Catalog (https://earthquake.usgs.gov/earthquakes/search/). The relevant data can be found by setting the Magnitude to a Custom Minimum equal to the magnitude of interest; setting the Date & Time to a Custom Start with the first day of interest and End to the last day of interest, leaving the UTC times to the default settings (00:00:00 & 23:59:59). Set Geographic Region to World, click Search beneath Output Options; note the number of earthquakes shown in the top left Search Results window.
clarification: The USGS earthquake database makes non-trivial revisions to their database after the initial values are posted. We thought that these revisions had stabilized when we resolved the question on 13 April but that has proven incorrect. To accommodate further revisions and still provide a resolution in a timely manner, this question will be resolved by consulting the source between 10:00 AM and 4:00 PM ET starting on Monday, 30 April. Resolution will be based on the value observed at the time of source consultation.
